    whyItMatters:
      'Canada\'s own Foreign Interference Commission found the PRC to be "by far the most significant" threat to Canadian democracy. Signing a secret information-and-cooperation channel with that same state\'s police ministry — the institution behind the transnational-repression "police stations" — raises a direct question: does the cooperation help fight transnational crime (the government\'s stated purpose), or does it expand the channels through which the PRC already conducts clandestine operations against people in Canada?',
