    bottomLine:
      'On the documented record: the Carney government\'s RCMP signed a secret cooperation agreement with the Chinese police ministry behind the illegal "police stations," at a time when Canada\'s own public inquiry calls the PRC the top threat to Canadian democracy. The government says it is about fighting transnational crime; opposition parties and a former senior Mountie say the secrecy and the counterparty make it a sovereignty risk. The public cannot evaluate which is true because the agreement is not public. That secrecy — on a deal with the police force of the country Canada\'s own inquiry calls its biggest threat — is itself the accountability problem.',
